.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH repose 1  "repose 3.1.0" 
.SH NAME
repose \- Repository manipulation tool for QAM
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBrepose\fR [\fB\-n\fR|\fB\-\-print\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] [\fB\-c\fR|\fB\-\-config\fR] [\fB\-d\fR|\fB\-\-debug\fR] [\fB\-q\fR|\fB\-\-quiet\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-color\fR] [\fB\-\-color\fR] [\fB\-\-format\fR] [\fB\-\-strict\-host\-key\-checking\fR] [\fB\-\-known\-hosts\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fIsubcommands\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Repository manipulation tool for QAM
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-n\fR, \fB\-\-print\fR
print commands for host and exit
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
show program\*(Aqs version number and exit
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-config\fR \fI<CONFIG>\fR [default: /etc/repose/products.yml]
path to repose configuration
.TP
\fB\-d\fR, \fB\-\-debug\fR
enable debug logging
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
suppress messages from repose
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-color\fR
disable ANSI color in console output (alias for \-\-color=never; honors NO_COLOR)
.TP
\fB\-\-color\fR \fI<COLOR>\fR [default: auto]
console color mode: \*(Aqauto\*(Aq (default; color on a TTY unless NO_COLOR), \*(Aqalways\*(Aq, or \*(Aqnever\*(Aq
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
auto
.IP \(bu 2
always
.IP \(bu 2
never
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-format\fR \fI<FORMAT>\fR [default: text]
console output format: \*(Aqtext\*(Aq (default) or \*(Aqjson\*(Aq (one event per line)
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
text
.IP \(bu 2
json
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-strict\-host\-key\-checking\fR \fI<STRICT_HOST_KEY_CHECKING>\fR [default: accept\-new]
SSH host\-key policy (OpenSSH semantics): \*(Aqyes\*(Aq refuses unknown hosts; \*(Aqaccept\-new\*(Aq (default) accepts unknown hosts on first contact but rejects changed keys; \*(Aqno\*(Aq/\*(Aqoff\*(Aq accepts both unknown and changed keys (pre\-1.12 behaviour)
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
yes
.IP \(bu 2
accept\-new
.IP \(bu 2
no
.IP \(bu 2
off
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-known\-hosts\fR \fI<KNOWN_HOSTS>\fR
path to a custom known_hosts file (overrides ~/.ssh/known_hosts)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
repose\-add(1)
add specified repository to target
.TP
repose\-remove(1)
remove repository from target
.TP
repose\-reset(1)
reset target repositories to only installed products repositories
.TP
repose\-install(1)
add specified repository to target and install product
.TP
repose\-clear(1)
clear all repositories from target
.TP
repose\-uninstall(1)
remove specified repository from target and uninstall product
.TP
repose\-list\-products(1)
list products on target
.TP
repose\-list\-repos(1)
list repositories on target
.TP
repose\-known\-products(1)
list known products by \*(Aqrepose\*(Aq
.TP
repose\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
.SH VERSION
v3.1.0
